Muni (actress) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muni_(actress) 0 Muni (born Marguerite Muni) June 23, 1929 – August 22, 1999) was a French actress who is best known for her appearances in the late French films of movie director Luis Buñuel. Though she is most often recognized by the last name moniker generally used in opening credits, she was occasionally listed under her full name. She is known for playing highly idiosyncratic characters, usually in supporting roles, in most of her films.
